reviewText:
Well, I liked the first Alan Wake a lot, and I waited something along the same line for this second game. But, in short:

Cons:
-The atmosphere from the first game is gone. Now the genre is more to adventure than horror;
-Repetitive gameplay;
-It feels like the whole game is about the arcade mode;
-The history is not good;
-It feels like the developers (and by this I mean the whole team) got lazy and just came up with a history that could use the same scenario many times, so they didn`t have to develop too much scenarios;
-Not much entertaining;
-Invisible walls (I'm putting this item here mainly because it was one of the things I praised on the first title);

Pros:
-The graphics, the videos and the voice acting are all well made. But this is not enough to compensate for all the other points;

4/10
